cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a framework for semantic segmentation of medical imaging using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an active learning approach using dropout at test time as Monte Carlo sampling to model the pixel-wise uncertainty and to analyze the image information to improve the training performance, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an approach to improve the training performance of a convolutional neural network for semantic segmentation of medical imaging, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.MED (Medical Imaging): The paper focuses on semantic segmentation of medical imaging, which falls under the domain of medical imaging. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper proposes an approach to analyze the image information to improve the training performance, which falls under the domain of information retrieval.
